topNews.title: Respected Comrade Kim Jong Un Inspects Sohae Satellite Launching Ground
content: Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and president of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, inspected the Sohae Satellite Launching Ground.

Accompanying him were Kim Jong Sik, Jang Chang Ha and other leading officials of the munitions industry and national defence scientific research sectors and officials concerned of the National Aerospace Development Administration.
Going round different parts of the ground, the respected General Secretary set forth a target for modernizing it and the detailed orientation and ways for doing so.

He learned about and evaluated the present state of the ground, and advanced the task to modernize it on an expansion basis so that various rockets could be launched to carry multi-purpose satellites, including a military reconnaissance satellite, in the future. He also set forth the task for building some facilities in the launching ground.

To enable large carrier rockets to be launched there, he assigned the tasks for reconstructing on an expansion basis the launching ground zone and the facilities for the general assembly and trial gearing of rocket and for the trial gearing of satellite, establishing extra facilities for the injection and supply of fuel and modernizing parts of the launch control facility and major technical posts on an expansion basis.

He also gave detailed instructions as regards the matters arising in modernizing the Sohae Satellite Launching Ground on an expansion basis, including the matters of expanding the capacity of the engine ground jet test site, ensuring the convenience of carrier rocket transport, improving the ecological environment around the launching ground and building a grandstand in the safe zone opposite to the launching ground.

He said that the Sohae Satellite Launching Ground is a place associated with the desire of President Kim Il Sung and Chairman Kim Jong Il for a space power and it is a significant place where our state successfully launched artificial satellites twice with its own efforts and technology, true to the lifetime intention of the President and the Chairman. And he stressed that it is the noble duty of our Party and space scientists and technicians in our era to turn the launching ground, associated with our state's great dream and ambition for a space power, into an ultramodern advanced base and a starting line of space conquest for the future suited to the prestige of the DPRK.

Encouraged by his teachings, the officials, scientists and technicians hardened their strong will to turn the Sohae Satellite Launching Ground into the best model suitable for the dignity and prestige of our state by devotedly carrying out the militant tasks set forth by the General Secretary, fully aware of their mission as space pioneers who should surely carry into practice the grand plan of the Party Central Committee for building a space power, true to the behest of the President and the Chairman.

topNews.title: Respected Comrade Kim Jong Un Inspects National Aerospace Development Administration (NADA)
content: Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) and president of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, inspected the National Aerospace Development Administration (NADA).
Accompanying him were Department Director Yu Jin and Vice Department Director Kim Jong Sik of the WPK Central Committee.
The respected General Secretary was greeted on the spot by leading officials of the NADA and the Academy of Defence Science.

Kim Jong Un learned in detail, from leading officials of the NADA, about the process of scientific research and development intended to hit the goals for attainment of space defence science and technology set forth at the 8th WPK Congress and the 4th Plenary Meeting of the 8th WPK Central Committee.

After acquainting himself with the development and preparations of optical photographing equipment, video transmitter and other communication data transceivers and various kinds of sensors and devices for satellite, he heard reports on the major test results recently conducted by the NADA.

He expressed his great satisfaction at the fact that they confirmed the aerospace photographing method, the operating characteristics of high-resolution photographing equipment and the reliability of image transmission system through the recent important tests.

Seeing the vertical and oblique high-resolution images on specific ground regions taken through the major tests, he highly appreciated the successes the NADA has recently made in settling the image composing and processing technology, the ability of processing a large volume of data communication, the accuracy of control command system, the technology of communication encryption, etc., true to the space development policy of the Party.

The development of a reconnaissance satellite takes an important share in attaining the five major goals for developing the defence power set forth at the 8th Party Congress, he said, stressing once again the strategic significance of the reconnaissance satellite in enhancing the war deterrent of the state and the capability of war preparedness.

Saying that the development of reconnaissance satellite is not merely a scientific research work for the development of information-gathering means, but a work for the protection of our sovereignty and national interests, the exercise of the legitimate rights to self-defence and the elevation of national prestige, he stressed that this urgent project for perfecting the country's war preparedness capacity by improving our state's war deterrent is the supreme revolutionary task, a political and military priority task to which our Party and government attach the most importance.

He called on the officials, scientists and technicians in the space and defence science research sectors to successfully accomplish the development of a Korean-style reconnaissance satellite within the period set by the Party Central Committee by getting united and closely cooperating with each other, true to the WPK's policies for aerospace development and national defence development.
The General Secretary also learned about the construction of the Academy of Space Science and a cosmic environment experiment center.

Noting that it is very important to lay a solid material and technical foundation for the field of space science research so as to attain the high sci-tech goal for space conquest set forth by our state, he stressed the need to give more state support to the space science research sector and examine the important measures for its steady development.

He said that it is our Party's important strategic and tactical policy on bolstering the national defence capability to keep a close eye on and distinguish the character of hostile military actions against the DPRK committed by the aggression troops of the U.S. imperialism and its vassal forces in and around the Korean Peninsula and enhance the capability for controlling situation and improve the rapid counteraction capability of the armed forces of the state according to the relevant situations. And he set forth the militant goals related to the development and operation of the reconnaissance satellite in the period of the five-year plan to implement this policy.

He noted that the purpose of developing and operating the military reconnaissance satellite is to provide the armed forces of the DPRK with real-time information on military actions against it by the aggression troops of the U.S. imperialism and its vassal forces in south Korea, Japan and the Pacific. And he said that the Party Central Committee fully supports the decision of the National Aerospace Development Administration on diversely putting a lot of military reconnaissance satellites into sun-synchronous polar orbit in the period of the five-year plan so as to possess the strong capability for gathering intelligence by satellites.

He expressed high expectation and belief that the space and national defence scientific research sectors would demonstrate to the full the heroic mettle of the defence scientific group remaining boundlessly faithful to the Party and revolution by rising up in the scientific and research campaign to thoroughly carry out the strategic plan of the Party Central Committee and making strenuous efforts.

Cherishing in their hearts the militant task set forth by the respected General Secretary, all the officials, scientists and technicians made a pledge of loyalty to defend the great dignity of our state with cutting-edge defence science, greatly encouraged by his deep trust that gives invincible strength.

topNews.title: Respected Comrade Kim Jong Un Plants Memorial Trees with Participants in 2nd Conference of Secretaries of WPK Primary Committees
content: Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and president of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, planted memorial trees together with the participants in the 2nd Conference of Secretaries of Primary Committees of the WPK on March 2, the Tree-planting Day.

Attending the tree-planting ceremony were Jo Yong Won, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau and secretary for Organizational Affairs of the WPK Central Committee, Ri Il Hwan, Kim Jae Ryong, O Il Jong, Kim Yong Hwan, Ju Chang Il and Kim Yo Jong.

The primary Party committee secretaries were filled with great excitement and delight as they came to plant memorial trees in the presence of the respected General Secretary in the Hwasong area where another ideal street symbolic of our Party's political idea of the people-first principle is being built.

When the General Secretary arrived, all the participants raised stormy cheers of "Hurrah!" for him, the great teacher and benevolent father who leads them step by step to become genuine political workers of the people's party, their "servant" party, repeatedly showing warm loving care and trust for them.
Jo Yong Won made an address in connection with the memorial tree-planting.
The participants in the 2nd Conference of Secretaries of Primary Committees of the WPK are here to do very worthwhile work on the Tree-planting Day, he said, adding:

It is very significant for us to have the honor of planting memorial trees in the presence of the respected General Secretary after receiving the new fighting programme for strengthening the primary Party committees as well as deep trust at the historic conference held amid the great attention of the Party members and other people across the country.
Tree-planting is due work of all citizens in this land and sacred patriotic work of planting seeds of happiness and shaping the future with their sweat and efforts.
Our primary Party committee secretaries are obliged to take the lead in this responsible work for executing the policy on the land development to which our Party attaches top priority.

Today's tree-planting will be an eternally unforgettable memory in the mind of the primary Party committee secretaries, the political workers of the people's party, their "servant" party and harden their will to devote themselves to the revolutionary work of taking care of the destiny of the country and people and thus bring about good results. And it will serve as an important occasion in further inspiring patriotism throughout the country.
We are here not only to plant trees but to plant our Party's policy and ardent patriotism and pure conscience that would remain unchanged forever.

These trees to be planted by us today will add beauty to the landscape of the Hwasong area near the holy land of the sun and grow in thick verdure, promising the rosy future of the capital city of Pyongyang.
The speaker called on all the participants to lavish their sweat and zeal on the work of lasting significance for further sprucing up the cradle of the people's life.
The respected Comrade Kim Jong Un broke ground first to signal the start of memorial tree-planting.

While transplanting trees with the participants, he called on the primary Party committee secretaries to lavish their patriotic zeal and party conscience on the work for implementing the Party's policies.

Saying that as the trees with firm roots can weather any storm, the Party that took its deep roots among the people and depends on them is invincible, he called on the secretaries of the primary Party committees to make redoubled efforts to turn our Party into a united group strong in its fighting efficiency that has taken its deep roots among the working masses.

The participants with high honor and delight devoted their sincerity to planting trees, visualizing the day when those young trees would grow up into giant ones ensuring the prosperity of our socialist state.
Kim Jong Un had a historic picture taken with the participants in tree-planting against the background of fir trees planted by him.

The excited participants expressed their deep gratitude to the General Secretary for bestowing the warm paternal love on them while inspiring them to become genuine officials of our Party which regards the idea of "The People Are God" as its motto and the people as lifeblood.

Through the memorial tree-planting, the secretaries of primary Party committees came to realize once again the fixed will of the Party Central Committee to make the revolution and construction run through with trust and love for the people, unconditionally serve them and finally build a communist society desired by all the people at any cost.

All the participants renewed their firm resolution to make signal progress in carrying out the tasks set forth at the 8th WPK Congress by developing the primary Party organizations into an integral whole of loyalists sharing the idea and intention with the Party Central Committee and acting as instructed by it, always mindful of the noble intention of the respected General Secretary.

The two fir trees, planted by Kim Jong Un in the Hwasong area where a new street for the people will appear, will steadily instill patriotism into all the people, adding green to socialist Korea where the people's dreams and ideal will come true.

topNews.title: Respected Comrade Kim Jong Un Has Photo Session with Participants in 2nd Conference of Secretaries of WPK Primary Committees
content: Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) and president of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, had a photo session with the participants in the 2nd Conference of Secretaries of Primary Committees of the WPK on March 2.

Present there were Jo Yong Won, member of the Presidium of the Political Bureau and secretary for Organizational Affairs of the WPK Central Committee, Ri Il Hwan, Kim Jae Ryong, O Il Jong, Kim Yong Hwan and Ju Chang Il.

The venue of the photo session was filled with the emotion and joy of the participants who would have the highest honor and happiness again in the wake of receiving the great action programme for further cementing the cornerstone and fighting efficiency of our Party at the conference of secretaries of primary Party committees held in the presence of the respected General Secretary.

When General Secretary Kim Jong Un arrived at the venue of the photo session, all the participants raised stormy cheers of "Hurrah!", paying the highest respects to him, the great prestige and symbol of our Party and the revolution who has strengthened the WPK into a powerful and militant general staff and a genuine people's party vigorously leading the sacred struggle for prosperity of our state and the people's well-being by brilliantly applying the Party's idea of giving importance to the strengthening of its basic organizations and line of strengthening the entire Party in the revolutionary practice.

The General Secretary encouraged the participants full of enthusiasm to devote all their efforts to the work for strengthening the basic organizations of the Party into the fortress of integral whole of loyalists and harmonious whole sharing the idea, intention and action with the Party Central Committee, while deeply cherishing once again its intention and idea that the fighting efficiency of the primary Party committees means that of our Party with the conference as an occasion.

Then he had a souvenir picture taken with the participants, expressing belief that the primary committee secretaries of the entire Party, who are standing at the first-line posts for developing the Party and implementing the Party's policies at a time when heavy and huge fighting tasks are raised before our revolution, would exert themselves in fulfilling their revolutionary duties with extraordinary consciousness and sense of responsibility as the frontline political workers and thus make positive contribution to bringing earlier a great new era when the people's ideal and desire would come true.

All the participants hardened their strong will to remain boundlessly committed to the political idea and historic mission of the genuine people's party, their "servant" party and further strengthen the basic Party organizations into the politico-ideological positions and vibrant militant ranks reliably upholding our Party and revolution, bearing deep in mind the noble intention and trust of the Party Central Committee, and thus dynamically accelerate the overall development of socialist construction.

topNews.title: Respected Comrade Kim Jong Un Makes Important Conclusion at 2nd Conference of Secretaries of Primary Committees of WPK
content: Kim Jong Un, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, made an important conclusion "Secretaries of Primary Party Committees Should Become Genuine Political Workers of the Motherly Party" at the 2nd Conference of Secretaries of Primary Committees of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) on February 28.

Saying that the entire Party and all the people pin very great expectations on the current conference of secretaries of the primary Party committees, the second of its kind in the history of the WPK, the respected Comrade Kim Jong Un referred to the significance of the conference convened at a crucial time of our revolution.

A primary Party committee is the organization that is directly responsible for protecting the political life of the Party members and other working people and its role decides the development of a unit and improvement of the livelihood of its employees, he said, adding that's why everyone pays attention to what tasks will be set forth at the conference and what change made in the future work of the primary Party committee.

Saying that it is possible to strengthen the whole Party and bring about an upswing on all fronts of socialist construction only when all the primary Party committees, the lower-echelon organizations of the Party and main fighting units for implementing the Party's policies, are well prepared and active, he stressed that in the light of that aspect it is of great significance at this crucial time to comprehensively examine and judge once again the fighting efficiency of the primary Party organizations and instill the idea and strategic intention of the Party Central Committee into the secretaries of the primary Party committees.

He appreciated that the conference again established a unanimous view on the importance and urgency of improving the work of the primary Party committees, analyzed and reviewed in detail the achievements and defects in the course of strengthening the primary Party committees and deeply discussed realistic ways.

He summarized the clear and positive changes made in the work of the primary Party committees in the past five years, including the fact that all the primary Party committees have focused their work on turning the units in their charge into the honest ones sharing idea and intention with the Party Central Committee and acting in concert with it, while exercising firm control and guidance over every work, ranging from the setting of goals to review and estimation, out of the firm stand that they should implement the Party's decisions and national economic plans without fail in keeping with their mission as the political staffs of the relevant units.

Saying in excited tones that there are many full-time Party officials within the WPK but secretaries of the primary Party committees take the greatest trouble as they are responsible for dealing with all sorts of affairs, he stressed that the foundations for strengthening the whole Party and implementing the Party's policies have been firmly cemented and the units representing the times increase, thanks to the devoted efforts of the secretaries of the primary Party committees who more deeply awakened themselves to their mission and duty to fulfill the solemn demands of the Party and the revolution.
He stressed the importance of sternly reviewing not only the past achievements but also the defects and drawing a lesson from them, for the conference is aimed at future development.

Saying that the building of the Party and its activities have further intensified in recent years and fresh innovations, bold creation and steady progress formed the main current of the times, but there still exist many serious defects in the work of secretaries of primary Party committees, he pointed out their universal mistakes.

Recalling that the conference rigorously reviewed the past work of secretaries of primary Party committees and discussed in depth the issues concerning the development of their work, he stressed the need for all the secretaries of the primary Party committees to innovate their work, as intended by the Party Central Committee and as required by the developing reality, while thoroughly getting rid of the negative elements latent in their work.

He referred to the important tasks to be upheld and fulfilled primarily at present by the secretaries of the primary Party committees, the political officials of the Party devotedly serving the people.

Saying that it is the steadfast will and the ultimate goal of the Party to consistently carry on the revolution and construction by dint of trust in and love for the people, unconditionally serve the people and build an ideal communist society for the people without fail, he stressed that our Party struggles to protect and support the people with sincerity, bring happiness to them and preserve their interests, not for any ism or prestige.

He pointed out that every line and policy put forward by the Party, its tested leadership and invincible fighting efficiency and our style socialist construction powerfully led by it are all characterized by the ideals of "The People Are God" and "Devoted Service for the People's Wellbeing."
He said that to be the Party of the people, the Party devotedly serving the people is the single reason of our Party's existence, its supreme symbol and permanent nature.

He stressed that our Party's goal to become the true people's Party bestowing all sorts of loving care on the people and its creed to become the Party that goes to great pains for the people can never change.

He said that the main purpose of building a new world on this land despite difficulties is not to demonstrate that we are capable of overcoming difficulties but to take care of the people with warmer sincerity and bring the happiest life to them.

Saying that the secretaries of the primary Party committees are responsible for forming a firm link between the intention and feelings of the Party Central Committee with the minds of the employees of the units in their charge, he underscored the need for them to fervently love the people and show all sincerity for them.
He noted that it is the highest honor of the secretaries of the primary Party committees to serve the people with sincerity.

He mentioned that it is the invariable assignment given by the Party Central Committee to the secretaries of the primary Party committees to become the true political workers of the people's Party, the Party devotedly serving the people.
He stressed that the work and humanity of primary Party committee secretaries will as ever be evaluated by how they play the role of an official of the motherly Party devotedly serving the people.

Urging them to be very humble before the people, regard it as their natural gift and the most worthwhile work to go through thick and thin and devotedly work to ensure the best convenience and life of the people, he said that to do so constitutes the main attitude and traits our Party now requires the secretaries of the primary Party committees to have.

Noting that it is not easy to do so, but from now on they should make a devoted forced march for the people in order to preserve the dignity and prestige of our Party, the party for the people and the party serving the people without an equal in the world, he said that it is high time for the Party officials to get closer to the people and treat them more kindly.
Then he referred to the issues the secretaries of the primary Party committees should concentrate on with an emphasis put on discharging the role of true mother and faithful servant.
He went on:

One of them is to train officials, Party members and other working people of their units into socialist persons with fine political and moral traits and the other is to dynamically conduct the organizational and political work to implement the decisions of the Party congress and the plenary meetings of the Party Central Committee. In other words, the first thing necessary is to transform the ideological consciousness of people, and the second thing is to turn into reality our Party's policies of promoting the people's well-being.
This fully complies with the true nature, mission and fighting purpose of our Party.
The secretaries of all the primary Party committees should be well aware of their mission as political officials of the Party serving the people, and make the Party work serve this purpose.
They should prepare the officials, Party members and other working people of their units to be politically and morally sound first of all.

For mothers, nothing brings more pleasure to them than to see their sons and daughters becoming admirable persons capable of devoting themselves to the country and the people, and authentic human beings faithfully serving society and the collectives and keeping moral obligations.
That's why mothers worry so much about their children and sometimes beat them to bring them up to be upright.

A priority task for our Party to do for our people is to bring up all persons to be wonderful beings with the same truthful loving care as those mothers do for their children. Important here is to make people learn and embody high political awareness and the revolutionary outlook on morality.

Kim Jong Un called on the secretaries of primary Party committees to direct their priority efforts to well preparing people in their units so as to fully guarantee them politically and morally before the Party and the revolution. He referred to the principled issues arising in earnestly and effectively doing education of the people to enhance their political awareness and outlook on morality.

Stagnation and retreat in the economic affairs can be recovered but the stagnation and retreat in the education of people would bring irrevocable consequences, he said, stressing the need for the primary Party organizations to effectively engage in the work for enhancing the political and moral consciousness of people before getting concerned about the implementation of economic plans and the state of production.

Education through revolutionary relics and the leadership feats of the Party is like the roots of our Party's ideological work and it can be called the starting point of the ideological education, he said, adding that it is entirely what the secretaries of the primary Party committees should do to make all the Party members and other working people find worth and honor of their life in the path of loyalty and patriotism and educate them to fulfill their moral obligation as human beings before society and the collective.

He defined it as the core of the work of preserving the revolutionary relics to make sure that the resilient bonds between the leader and the people get stronger and our people's reverence for the leader become part of their ideological and moral traits. He underlined the need for the secretaries of the primary Party committees to give precedence to building well and managing and operating regularly the educational bases like Kimilsungism-Kimjongilism Study Hall, room for the education in the revolutionary history and room dedicated to the history of the units and thus make sure that the Party members and other working people nurture loyalty, faith and moral obligation for the Party and carry on the noble fighting spirit displayed by those of the preceding generations of the revolution.

High political awareness and noble moral traits can become stronger and part of life only through organizational life and practice, he said, calling on the secretaries of the primary Party committees to set strong organizational discipline and make organizational and ideological life a regular and standardized one in all cases. He said that it is imperative to make all persons train themselves politically and morally under continued guidance of organization and support by the collective.

Revolutionary practice is like a wonderful school for bringing up people, he said, stressing that the secretaries of the primary Party committees should not just wait for examples of the times to be produced from their units but purposefully organize the work to make all their employees patriotic working people and innovators who cherish love for factory, job and hometown in the revolutionary practices.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees should respect and put forward before anyone else those faithfully fulfilling their own duties without wishing for any honor and appraisement, and inspire the masses with the positive example of the said persons so as to increase the ranks of faithful socialist working people, he said, stressing the need for the secretaries to lead the employees of their units to teach and learn from each other, share good experience and admonish against defects so that they would do things beneficial to the collective and display noble and beautiful moral traits.

Kim Jong Un emphasized that the primary Party committee secretaries should wage dynamic organizational and political work for implementing the decisions of the 8th Party Congress and the plenary meetings of the Party Central Committee and bring about substantial achievements. He went on:

The decisions of the Party Congress and the plenary meetings of the Party Central Committee reflect the firm determination and will of our Party to clear our people of their troubles at the earliest date and make them lead more stable and improved living at any cost.
Therefore, our Party officials, secretaries of the primary Party committees should fulfill their responsibilities so that major decisions of the Party bear good fruit.
It is important to definitely turn the struggle for implementing the Party decisions into the work of the popular masses themselves.
What our Party believes most in the present struggle for winning new victory in socialist construction in defiance of unprecedented difficulties and trials is the mental power of the popular masses.
Though right decisions are adopted by the Party, they will remain an empty talk if masses are not motivated.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees should make the Party members and other working people turn out voluntarily in implementing the Party's policies by making them clearly understand that those policies are just for the sake of themselves and that no one can replace them in implementing the policies and that only when each unit thoroughly carries out the Party's decisions, the state affairs will be successful and the people's living will improve.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees should make sure that all the employees become clearly aware of the work plans of their units in implementing the decisions of the Party Congress and the plenary meetings of the Party Central Committee, and steadily remind them of the plans, not just feeling satisfied with one or two reminding.

They should be strict with the popular masses to make them review the daily implementation of the Party's decisions and get actively engaged in it, regarding them as standard and goal of their work. They should also help the employees display creativity through discussion with them of the innovative ways for the development of their units.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees, bearing this in mind, have to wage effective and active political work to make sure that every worksite brims with the active drive for implementing the Party decisions and the national economic plans.

In order to make the officials, Party members and other working people creditably carry out their tasks with proper stand and attitude to the implementation of the Party decisions, the secretaries of the primary Party committees should effectively do the summing-up and evaluation.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees should take beforehand measures to solve problems that may arise in implementing the Party decisions and take care of bottleneck problems themselves to ensure the timely solution so as to keep the masses highly engaged.

Kim Jong Un said that an important issue which the secretaries of the primary Party committees should pay heed to in implementing the Party decisions is to train scientific and technical forces of their units and deepen the Party guidance to make sure that it pays off.
He continued:
Whether scientific and technical talents pay off or not depends on Party officials.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees who embody well the Party's idea of attaching importance to science and technology and talents and who have sizeable knowledge of science and technology about their own fields can be effective in doing the work with the talents.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees should know all the technical forces and talents of their units, encourage them so that each of them could do their share and provide conditions for work and be responsible for their pursuit and results.

The science and technology development plans should be included in the work plans of the primary Party committees as an important items, and through the work for implementing them, the level of the technicians and skilled workers should be raised and their ranks be expanded.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees should pay deep attention to the effective operation of sci-tech dissemination bases all the time to make officials and employees strengthen scientific and technological study.

Primary Party committees have to assign sci-tech study task to officials and employees and review their implementation so as to make them regard sci-tech study as the requirement under the Party policies and turn the course of study into the one of steadily raising the level of their technical skill.

They should provide Party support to establish the traits of always giving precedence to science and technology in carrying out the Party decisions and the national economic plans and solving knotty problems by dint of science and technology and through mass technical innovation.
Whether Party decisions given to a unit are implemented or not importantly depends on whether the Party, the administration and technical officials achieve trinity or not, Kim Jong Un said.

He taught the work principles to be maintained by the secretaries of the primary Party committees, leading members in the trinity body, which include the issue of putting forward administrative and technical officials and respecting their opinions, the issue of providing Party support for the employees to accept the instructions of the administrative and technical officials as important ones and carry them out in time.

He also mentioned the importance of welfare supply service in boosting the enthusiasm of the Party members and other working people who turned out in implementing the Party's decisions. Stressing the need for the secretaries of the primary Party committees to bring about evident improvement in the supply service work through strenuous efforts with firm determination to solve the problems concerning the living conditions of the employees at any cost, he said that the supply service work of each unit is what the secretaries of the primary Party committees should be responsible for from A to Z and that the supply service work must be the one from which employees can truly benefit under any conditions.

Pointing out the issue of thoroughly obeying the state unified guidance and management over the economic work and the issue of improving the logistic work while putting the state interests above, he called for rejuvenating the foundation of logistic work to suit to the specific features of one's own unit and changing conditions and for setting rational logistic supply system and method.

Kim Jong Un stressed the need to thoroughly prevent accidents in all units. He said that the secretaries of the primary Party committees should establish the revolutionary system and order while regularly acquainting and examining details of the state of their own units with responsibility, and ensure that all the officials, Party members and other working people work and live as required by the system and order. He also said that the secretaries of the primary Party committees should conduct in a far-sighted way the work of removing all the accident-prone elements from the stand of prioritizing security, calling for taking effective measures to settle faulty issues concerning the life and security of our people in particular.
Kim Jong Un set forth the ways for making the primary Party committees the groups with strong fighting efficiency and cohesion.

Whoever is the secretary of primary Party committee should throw oneself into turning it into a solid political and ideological position, vibrant combat rank of reliably standing guard over a post entrusted to them by the Party and the revolution, he said, calling for making the primary Party committees the integral whole of loyalty sharing the same thinking, intention and action with the Party Central Committee, both in name and reality.

He stressed that the starting point and the general orientation of the work of primary Party committees is to help officials and Party members cherish immutable faith in keeping to the only path of following the Party Central Committee however the situation and the environment may change.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees should make the officials and Party members regard it as the most sacred duty and supreme honor to follow the revolutionary idea of the Party Central Committee as the unconditional truth, to rely on it in doing everything and to unconditionally support and uphold with single mind the intention and plan of the Party Central Committee, he said.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees should put efforts into staffing well the primary Party committees, political staff of their own units and enhancing the role of their members, Kim Jong Un stressed.
Strengthening the primary Party committees presupposes strengthening Party cells, he said, adding:
When all the Party cells in their units become healthy and vibrant cells, the primary Party committees can become vibrant groups with strong fighting efficiency and cohesion.
The secretaries of the primary Party committees should keep deepening the work with the Party cell secretaries responsible for the cell work, not forgetting it even a minute.

Those core members who are supported and trusted by the Party members should be made to take charge of the Party cells. The secretaries of the primary Party committees should exact high demand on the Party cell secretaries so that they can put all efforts into their work while constantly reminding themselves of the 10-point tasks and 12-point traits of Party cell secretaries, and strive to enhance the level of their working ability.

In order to make the Party cells healthy and vibrant ones closely knitted in the bonds of kinship, it is necessary to create examples, generalize experience and put all the Party cells in each unit on a height required by the Party Central Committee.

He said that as they are also members of the Party cells, the secretaries of the primary Party committees should give positive influence on the Party members and help the secretaries of the Party cells by setting an example in the manner of treating the Party cell secretaries and in the attitude of receiving Party assignments and executing them.

Saying that the work of preparing the Party members and other working people politically and morally and the work of implementing the Party decisions depend on how the secretaries of the primary Party committees conduct the work with people, he taught the issues for the secretaries of the primary Party committees to fundamentally improve the work with the people.

Saying that in order to do the work with people well, the secretaries of the primary Party committees should find themselves among the employees to correctly examine their mind and personality, he stressed that they should strive to deepen feelings with the employees and lend an ear to their honest voices and appeal while doing work together with them and talking to them all the time.
He called upon the secretaries of the primary Party committees to conduct the work with people in a creative way to suit to their characters.
He also called upon them to steadily search the effective ways and use them flexibly, mindful that they can not expect any achievement if they use stereotyped way in doing the work with people.

He said that just as a mother speaks differently to her son and daughter and treats them differently in their growth stages, the secretaries of the primary Party committees should do the work with people creatively to suit to the characters of each person and the given situations though their employees number hundreds and thousands.

He indicated in detail the ways of doing the work with different groups of people like the youth who are strong in the enterprising spirit and are always vibrant, women who are always considerate of their children and family life and those who made a mistake in their work and life.
He called upon the secretaries of the primary Party committees to take warm care of their employees.

He said that what is common in the work of those units in which everything goes well is that the secretaries of the primary Party committees strive to solve even one more problem arising in the living of the employees while paying deep attention to it.

Saying that employees are moved when the secretaries of primary Party committees call in on them to ask about difficulties and sufferings, and they feel very grateful for the Party officials and set store by their care when they get to know that the Party officials take pains for them, he called on the secretaries of primary Party committees to take warmer care of the employees and dedicate sincerity to helping them out of difficulties, always paying deep attention to them.

He said that the secretaries of primary Party committees should make it their habit to relieve the employees of their sufferings and resolve their knotty problems at any cost, conscious of their duty as the servants of the people, and kindly treat all the employees as family members, just like a mother who treats her children without discrimination.
He stressed the need for the secretaries of the primary Party committees to maintain the principle while seriously and maturely doing the work with people.

Saying that it is the greatest taboo to regard the words of one or two persons as absolute or thoughtlessly deal with the issues arising among people on the basis of superficial view or guess, he underlined the need for the secretaries of primary Party committees to do the work with people in an unbiased and experienced manner, never blinded by subjectivity and prejudice.

He urged them to acquire a habit of repeatedly scrutinizing necessary information before making decisions on the issues related with the political destiny of people and prudently resolving them in consideration of the interests of the Party and the revolution.

Saying that for them to take warm care of and respect people never means that they should remain good-natured, blindly appeasing them, overlooking their faults and currying favor with them, he called on the secretaries of the primary Party committees to treat the employees with warm humanity and educate them in a principled manner while waging a severe struggle against negative elements.
He said that the secretaries of the primary Party committees should acquire high qualifications in order to do the work with people well.

Stressing that today's socialist construction, whereby the grandiose goal is being accomplished in the arduous and difficult situation, requires the secretaries of primary Party committees, tasked with educating, organizing and mobilizing people, to possess high abilities as never before, he said that the main task for improving their abilities is to be well versed in the Party's line and policy and proficient in the Party work.

The secretaries of the primary Party committees should put above anything else the study of the documents on the Party Congress and the plenary meetings of the Party Central Committee that comprehensively deal with the Party's line and policies, and completely grasp them by repeatedly studying them on a regular basis so that they can be able to freely explain them among the masses, he noted.

He called on the secretaries of primary Party committees to make it a part of their everyday life to read the Party organ in order to steadily improve their political and practical qualifications by grasping the ideas and intentions of the Party Central Committee on a normal basis and learning the methods of implementing the Party policies.

He stressed the need for them to continue intensifying the study for the Party work, learn more professional knowledge for their sectors and knowledge and technique for their units and steadily acquire lots of many-sided knowledge with the open-minded attitude as required by the developing era.
He underlined the need for them to gain experience and draw lessons from their work and have meticulous organizing ability, strong control and implacable executive ability.

Noting that if the secretaries of the primary Party committees are to do the work with people well, they should have noble popular traits, he said that they will be disliked by people if they have a rude style of work, although they are politically and ideologically sound and have excellent working ability.
He stressed that high Party spirit, fidelity to principle and noble humanity constitute the main traits befitting the secretaries of the primary Party committees that captivate people.

He called on them to have the warm heart to greatly love people and take sincere care of them and lead them with the stand to bear responsibility for the present life of the employees and their future.

Noting that modesty, an unassuming character and uprightness are essential traits of the primary Party committee secretaries as they do the work with people at all times, he said that they should always treat employees courteously and in a free-hearted manner with a smile on their faces and lead a simple life, not pursuing selfish interests and desires.

He said that they should keep their appearance neat and clean, use polite language and make positive efforts to have lots of cultural attainments and optimistic sentiments capable of touching people and creating an optimistic climate among them.
He specially stressed the need for the Party committee secretaries of ministries and national institutions and the secretaries of ri Party committees to enhance their responsibilities and roles.

Saying that the Party committee secretaries of ministries and national institutions are responsible for the Party work of the state administrative guidance institutions organizing and guiding the work for implementing the lines and policies of the Party nationwide, he called on them to lead all officials of their institutions to steadily cultivate themselves through their Party life, political life, and to properly plan and guide the work for the implementation of the Party policies, bearing in mind that they have very responsible tasks in a very responsible period.

He said that the Party Central Committee attaches great significance to enhancing the role of the Party committee secretaries of ministries and national institutions at present when epochal progress should be made in the overall state work and practical successes be achieved in the development of the national economy every year.

Noting that the duty of secretaries of ri Party committees is very heavy in the historic struggle for giving a complete face-lift to the countryside, he called on the secretaries of ri Party committees across the country to redouble their efforts, cherishing the high honor and sense of responsibility for conducting the Party work in the great new era for rural revolution.

He also stressed the need for departments of the Party Central Committee and provincial, city and county Party committees to pay deep attention to the work for enhancing the role of the secretaries of primary Party committees.

He underscored the need to direct efforts to the work for consolidating the ranks of primary Party committee secretaries and properly conduct the work for educating them and raising their practical abilities.

Noting that the Party Central Committee should set it as its policy and a state policy to translate the desire of people into reality and ensure that people benefit from the policy by letting all the primary Party organizations thoroughly implement it, he said that to do so is not only the action method peculiar to our Party fully discharging its duty as the Party serving the people but also the idea on the role of the primary Party committees and the idea of attaching importance to the primary Party committees advocated by the Party Central Committee.

Saying that the true appearance of the primary Party committee secretaries is characterized by the attitude of the servant who puts his heart and soul into bringing welfare to the people as much as possible, being thoughtful and meticulous like mother, he said that all the secretaries of the primary Party committees should become such servants to make sure that the Party lives up to the expectations of the people who have lavished their praise of it as the motherly Party despite the stern tempest of history and remains faithful to its political idea and historic mission as the Party serving the people.

He ardently called on all secretaries of the primary Party committees to turn out in the sacred struggle for providing our people with a happy life as early as possible and turning our country into a great powerful socialist state, well aware of their duty as political officials of the Party serving the people.

The important conclusion made by the respected Comrade Kim Jong Un at the 2nd Conference of Secretaries of Primary Committees of the WPK serves as a powerful militant banner for turning all the basic Party organizations into the elite ranks of loyalty with the organizing ability and fighting efficiency and vitality as required by a new era of overall national prosperity and for strongly encouraging all the Party members and other working people to the drive for implementing the grandiose struggle programme indicated at the Party Congress under the uplifted banner of great Kimilsungism-Kimjongilism.
